00:49:22,360 --> 00:49:22,800
Well.

1430
00:49:23,040 --> 00:49:26,460
This tells me explicitly how the component is.

1431
00:49:26,460 --> 00:49:28,160
These are the components of the small vector transform.

1432
00:49:28,880 --> 00:49:32,300
They transform by getting multiplied by

1433
00:49:32,300 --> 00:49:35,720
this collection of things dy by dx.

1434
00:49:36,740 --> 00:49:40,130
Now I can tell you what

1435
00:49:40,130 --> 00:49:43,520
the definition of a contravariant vector is.

1436
00:49:43,980 --> 00:49:47,090
The definition of a contravariant vector is

1437
00:49:47,090 --> 00:49:50,200
a collection of things which have components

1438
00:49:50,200 --> 00:49:53,320
in both the x frame of reference and

1439
00:49:53,320 --> 00:49:56,440
also components in the y frame of reference.

1440
00:49:56,440 --> 00:49:56,680
reference,

1441
00:49:56,680 --> 00:49:58,360
and those components,

1442
00:49:58,360 --> 00:49:59,880
let's now be general,

1443
00:49:59,880 --> 00:50:01,280
let's call it V,

1444
00:50:01,280 --> 00:50:02,760
V for vector.

1445
00:50:04,480 --> 00:50:07,330
The components of the vector V1 through

1446
00:50:07,330 --> 00:50:10,180
Vn in the Y frame of reference,

1447
00:50:10,180 --> 00:50:11,420
let me put down here

1448
00:50:11,420 --> 00:50:12,160
in brackets,

1449
00:50:12,160 --> 00:50:14,600
that these are the components relative

1450
00:50:14,600 --> 00:50:17,040
to the Y frame of reference,

1451
00:50:17,360 --> 00:50:18,320
in other words,

1452
00:50:18,320 --> 00:50:20,500
relative to the Y coordinate system,

1453
00:50:20,500 --> 00:50:25,780
are equal to the derivatives,

1454
00:50:26,440 --> 00:50:31,640
of Yn with respect to Xm

1455
00:50:31,640 --> 00:50:36,840
times Vm in the X coordinate frame.

1456
00:50:37,200 --> 00:50:38,000
In other words,

1457
00:50:38,000 --> 00:50:39,730
they behave exactly the same

1458
00:50:39,730 --> 00:50:41,460
way as these little differential

1459
00:50:44,280 --> 00:50:47,120
vector components of a little displacement behave.

1460
00:50:47,300 --> 00:50:49,120
Now don't ask me why this is true,

1461
00:50:49,120 --> 00:50:49,780
this is definition.

1462
00:50:50,300 --> 00:50:54,340
This is definition of an object which transforms

1463
00:50:59,220 --> 00:50:59,820
contravariantly,

1464
00:50:59,820 --> 00:51:01,000
it's just a word,

1465
00:51:01,000 --> 00:51:04,200
for our purposes it doesn't mean anything right now.

1466
00:51:09,440 --> 00:51:12,140
That's the definition of a vector,

1467
00:51:12,140 --> 00:51:14,500
or a contravariant vector,

1468
00:51:14,500 --> 00:51:15,820
that its components,

1469
00:51:15,960 --> 00:51:16,860
whatever they are,

1470
00:51:16,860 --> 00:51:18,700
that they transform when you go

1471
00:51:18,700 --> 00:51:20,540
from one frame of reference to another,

1472
00:51:20,760 --> 00:51:23,140
through this collection of quantities,

1473
00:51:23,140 --> 00:51:25,600
the Yn by the Xm.

1474
00:51:26,440 --> 00:51:27,900
What quantities are there altogether?

1475
00:51:29,520 --> 00:51:30,160
How many?

1476
00:51:30,160 --> 00:51:30,820
D squared.

1477
00:51:31,000 --> 00:51:31,360
D squared,

1478
00:51:31,360 --> 00:51:32,280
right.

1479
00:51:32,280 --> 00:51:35,680
Any Y can be differentiated with respect to any X,

1480
00:51:35,680 --> 00:51:36,060
yes,

1481
00:51:36,800 --> 00:51:40,920
and so there are D squared such coefficient functions here,

1482
00:51:41,860 --> 00:51:43,980
and this is the way you transform a vector.

1483
00:51:45,720 --> 00:51:48,180
To those who are familiar with linear algebra,

1484
00:51:48,180 --> 00:51:50,500
this is of course a matrix,

1485
00:51:51,140 --> 00:51:52,840
and this is a column vector,

1486
00:51:52,840 --> 00:51:54,040
and here's a column vector,

1487
00:51:54,040 --> 00:51:55,780
but we don't need that right now.

1488
00:51:56,440 --> 00:51:59,580
It's a transformation property of a contravariant vector.

1489
00:52:01,160 --> 00:52:02,870
Does contravariant refer to the

1490
00:52:02,870 --> 00:52:04,580
nature of the coordinate system?

1491
00:52:05,080 --> 00:52:05,360
No,

1492
00:52:05,360 --> 00:52:06,860
it refers to the way it transforms,

1493
00:52:06,860 --> 00:52:08,440
the way it transforms,

1494
00:52:08,440 --> 00:52:09,100
that's right.

1495
00:52:09,240 --> 00:52:10,380
The way it transforms.

1496
00:52:10,680 --> 00:52:13,330
We're going to discover

1497
00:52:13,330 --> 00:52:15,980
other objects called covariant tensors,

1498
00:52:16,100 --> 00:52:18,780
but so far this is just a mere vector,

1499
00:52:18,780 --> 00:52:20,720
something that's pretty easy to visualize.

1500
00:52:21,420 --> 00:52:23,920
Now a tensor of rank two is an

1501
00:52:23,920 --> 00:52:26,420
object which is not so easy to visualize.

1502
00:52:26,440 --> 00:52:30,400
You should think of it somehow as having two directions,

1503
00:52:30,540 --> 00:52:32,660
that's a thing that has built

1504
00:52:32,660 --> 00:52:34,780
into it two directions instead of one,

1505
00:52:34,960 --> 00:52:38,400
but there's an easy way to think

1506
00:52:38,400 --> 00:52:41,840
about the simplest tensor that's made up,

1507
00:52:43,060 --> 00:52:46,200
the simplest tensor of rank two can be

1508
00:52:46,200 --> 00:52:49,340
simply thought of as a product of two vectors.

1509
00:52:49,980 --> 00:52:51,320
Given two vectors,

1510
00:52:51,320 --> 00:52:53,070
and they could be the same

1511
00:52:53,070 --> 00:52:54,820
vector or they could be different vectors,

1512
00:52:54,940 --> 00:52:55,560
it doesn't matter.

1513
00:52:55,560 --> 00:52:57,340
Let's call one of them A,

1514
00:52:57,340 --> 00:53:00,760
and it has components M,

1515
00:53:00,760 --> 00:53:02,600
A sub A M,

1516
00:53:03,860 --> 00:53:07,120
and now let's take another vector which we'll call B,

1517
00:53:09,980 --> 00:53:11,900
and write its components down.

1518
00:53:13,580 --> 00:53:17,520
How many such things are there altogether?

1519
00:53:19,620 --> 00:53:20,700
I can multiply,

1520
00:53:20,700 --> 00:53:24,040
there's a whole collection of objects I can make up.

1521
00:53:24,320 --> 00:53:25,540
I can take any one of them,

1522
00:53:25,560 --> 00:53:27,360
I can take any one of the components of A

1523
00:53:27,360 --> 00:53:29,160
and multiply it by any one of the components of B,

1524
00:53:29,380 --> 00:53:30,380
and that's an object.

1525
00:53:30,880 --> 00:53:33,440
It's an object that may or may not be interesting.

1526
00:53:33,660 --> 00:53:34,180
We're going to see,

1527
00:53:34,180 --> 00:53:35,780
we're going to discover ones which are interesting.

1528
00:53:36,060 --> 00:53:38,860
How many such components does such an object have?

1529
00:53:39,540 --> 00:53:41,080
This has D components,

1530
00:53:41,080 --> 00:53:42,460
this has D components.

1531
00:53:42,920 --> 00:53:45,660
The number of components altogether is D squared.

1532
00:53:46,620 --> 00:53:50,920
So this is an object which has D squared components,

1533
00:53:51,720 --> 00:53:53,630
and the individual components

1534
00:53:53,630 --> 00:53:55,540
are labeled with two directions.

1535
00:53:56,439 --> 00:53:59,119
This is a special case

1536
00:53:59,119 --> 00:54:01,800
of a tensor of rank two.

1537
00:54:02,220 --> 00:54:04,160
It has two components,

1538
00:54:04,160 --> 00:54:04,680
sorry,

1539
00:54:04,680 --> 00:54:05,600
it has two indices,

1540
00:54:06,540 --> 00:54:11,260
and altogether D squared individual components.

1541
00:54:11,640 --> 00:54:15,420
How does it transform when I change coordinate systems?

1542
00:54:16,020 --> 00:54:16,540
Well,

1543
00:54:16,540 --> 00:54:17,300
this is easy.

1544
00:54:17,420 --> 00:54:21,260
I already know how the vectors transform,

1545
00:54:22,100 --> 00:54:24,400
so all I need to do is,

1546
00:54:25,700 --> 00:54:27,360
let's work it out.

1547
00:54:27,720 --> 00:54:28,820
Let's work it out.

1548
00:54:29,480 --> 00:54:31,000
Let's take A,

1549
00:54:31,000 --> 00:54:33,220
let's compute,

1550
00:54:33,920 --> 00:54:34,520
A,

1551
00:54:34,520 --> 00:54:35,300
N,

1552
00:54:35,300 --> 00:54:36,720
A,

1553
00:54:36,720 --> 00:54:37,180
M,

1554
00:54:37,180 --> 00:54:37,740
B,

1555
00:54:37,740 --> 00:54:41,020
N in the Y frame of reference.

1556
00:54:41,740 --> 00:54:42,860
In other words,

1557
00:54:42,860 --> 00:54:44,400
where the coordinates are written relative

1558
00:54:44,400 --> 00:54:45,940
to the Y frame of reference.

1559
00:54:46,320 --> 00:54:46,920
Well,

1560
00:54:46,920 --> 00:54:49,160
here's a rule for connecting components

1561
00:54:49,160 --> 00:54:51,400
of a vector in the Y frame

1562
00:54:51,400 --> 00:54:54,600
with components of the same vector in the X frame.

1563
00:54:54,600 --> 00:54:55,980
So let's just apply it.

1564
00:54:58,060 --> 00:54:59,140
Let's relate these.

1565
00:54:59,380 --> 00:54:59,580
Now,

1566
00:54:59,580 --> 00:55:00,240
first of all,

1567
00:55:00,240 --> 00:55:00,600
there's A.

1568
00:55:01,340 --> 00:55:02,260
A is a vector.

1569
00:55:02,260 --> 00:55:03,720
They are not dummy indices.

1570
00:55:03,940 --> 00:55:04,440
They're picked.

1571
00:55:04,620 --> 00:55:05,280
This could be three,

1572
00:55:05,280 --> 00:55:06,180
this could be two,

1573
00:55:06,360 --> 00:55:07,900
but they're not summed over.

1574
00:55:08,140 --> 00:55:10,080
Dummy index is one which is summed over.

1575
00:55:11,360 --> 00:55:11,980
All right,

1576
00:55:11,980 --> 00:55:12,840
so here's the matching.

1577
00:55:13,980 --> 00:55:16,080
This index matches this index,

1578
00:55:16,420 --> 00:55:18,420
so we better put an M up here.

1579
00:55:19,180 --> 00:55:20,850
And then we differentiate it

1580
00:55:20,850 --> 00:55:22,520
with respect to a dummy index.

1581
00:55:22,960 --> 00:55:24,520
I don't want to call it dummy index,

1582
00:55:24,600 --> 00:55:26,720
but I'll call it X,

1583
00:55:26,720 --> 00:55:27,060
R,

1584
00:55:29,980 --> 00:55:30,940
times A,

1585
00:55:30,940 --> 00:55:31,420
R.

1586
00:55:31,860 --> 00:55:33,600
That's just this piece of it over here.

1587
00:55:35,040 --> 00:55:35,520
A,

1588
00:55:35,520 --> 00:55:36,180
M of Y,

1589
00:55:36,180 --> 00:55:37,820
this should be of X.

1590
00:55:39,140 --> 00:55:39,620
A,

1591
00:55:39,620 --> 00:55:42,080
M in the Y frame of reference

1592
00:55:42,580 --> 00:55:44,060
is the derivative of Y,

1593
00:55:44,060 --> 00:55:45,380
M with respect to X,

1594
00:55:45,380 --> 00:55:45,680
R

1595
00:55:45,680 --> 00:55:46,460
times A,

1596
00:55:46,460 --> 00:55:48,240
R summed over R.

1597
00:55:48,660 --> 00:55:49,140
Now,

1598
00:55:49,140 --> 00:55:50,140
that's only half the expression.

1599
00:55:50,360 --> 00:55:53,040
The other half involves what happens to B.

1600
00:55:53,260 --> 00:55:54,480
So let's write that down.

1601
00:55:54,600 --> 00:55:55,320
Again,

1602
00:55:55,320 --> 00:55:57,940
we should match indices.

1603
00:55:58,340 --> 00:56:00,400
Here we have the nth index,

1604
00:56:00,780 --> 00:56:03,420
so that means some derivative of Y,

1605
00:56:03,420 --> 00:56:05,040
N.

1606
00:56:06,040 --> 00:56:08,160
Now I need another dummy index.

1607
00:56:08,660 --> 00:56:12,060
I need another dummy index I've already summed over R.

1608
00:56:12,260 --> 00:56:13,800
I can't call it R again,

1609
00:56:14,000 --> 00:56:16,200
so I'll call it S.

1610
00:56:16,440 --> 00:56:17,060
X,

1611
00:56:17,060 --> 00:56:19,500
S times D,

1612
00:56:19,500 --> 00:56:23,080
X times A,

1613
00:56:24,600 --> 00:56:25,320
times B,

1614
00:56:25,320 --> 00:56:30,380
S in the X reference frame.

1615
00:56:32,280 --> 00:56:35,620
All I've done is taken A and B

1616
00:56:35,620 --> 00:56:37,660
and separately transformed them

1617
00:56:37,660 --> 00:56:40,480
from the X coordinates to the Y coordinates.

1618
00:56:40,860 --> 00:56:42,740
But now let me just regroup it.

1619
00:56:42,920 --> 00:56:45,540
Let me just regroup it by taking this over here

1620
00:56:46,380 --> 00:56:47,800
and writing A,

1621
00:56:47,800 --> 00:56:48,300
R,

1622
00:56:48,300 --> 00:56:50,080
X.

1623
00:56:54,600 --> 00:56:54,700
A,

1624
00:56:54,700 --> 00:56:55,860
M times B,

1625
00:56:55,860 --> 00:56:58,360
N is called T,

1626
00:56:58,360 --> 00:56:58,720
M,

1627
00:56:58,720 --> 00:56:58,940
N,

1628
00:56:59,000 --> 00:57:03,420
a tensor of rank two with index M and N.

1629
00:57:03,720 --> 00:57:06,660
So I can call this then T,

1630
00:57:06,660 --> 00:57:07,300
M,

1631
00:57:07,300 --> 00:57:07,780
N

1632
00:57:10,360 --> 00:57:13,320
with components in the Y frame of reference.

1633
00:57:14,580 --> 00:57:16,940
That's equal to D,

1634
00:57:16,940 --> 00:57:17,420
Y,

1635
00:57:17,420 --> 00:57:19,340
M by D,

1636
00:57:19,340 --> 00:57:19,820
X,

1637
00:57:19,820 --> 00:57:20,120
R,

1638
00:57:20,800 --> 00:57:21,420
D,

1639
00:57:21,420 --> 00:57:21,880
Y,

1640
00:57:21,880 --> 00:57:23,880
N by D,

1641
00:57:23,880 --> 00:57:24,400
X,

1642
00:57:24,400 --> 00:57:24,580
R,

1643
00:57:24,580 --> 00:57:24,780
S,

1644
00:57:24,780 --> 00:57:26,540
and what shall I call this?

1645
00:57:31,140 --> 00:57:32,220
It's also some T.

1646
00:57:32,380 --> 00:57:35,180
It's also the components of a tensor

1647
00:57:35,180 --> 00:57:37,040
built up out of A times B,

1648
00:57:37,040 --> 00:57:38,900
okay?

1649
00:57:40,160 --> 00:57:40,820
Not T,

1650
00:57:40,820 --> 00:57:41,000
M,

1651
00:57:41,000 --> 00:57:41,460
N but T,

1652
00:57:41,460 --> 00:57:41,740
R,

1653
00:57:41,740 --> 00:57:41,980
S.

1654
00:57:43,760 --> 00:57:44,160
T,

1655
00:57:44,160 --> 00:57:44,560
R,

1656
00:57:44,560 --> 00:57:44,780
S.

1657
00:57:45,220 --> 00:57:47,160
The first entry has to do with A,

1658
00:57:47,240 --> 00:57:48,780
the second entry has to do with B,

1659
00:57:48,880 --> 00:57:51,940
so I should really invert the order of them.

1660
00:57:53,680 --> 00:57:54,080
B,

1661
00:57:54,080 --> 00:57:54,480
S,

1662
00:57:54,480 --> 00:57:54,560
R,

1663
00:57:54,560 --> 00:57:54,560
S,

1664
00:57:54,560 --> 00:57:54,560
R,

1665
00:57:54,560 --> 00:57:54,560
S.

1666
00:57:54,580 --> 00:57:54,800
S,

1667
00:57:54,800 --> 00:57:55,400
X,

1668
00:57:55,400 --> 00:57:56,610
just to make it look

1669
00:57:56,610 --> 00:57:57,820
the same as on this side.

1670
00:57:58,160 --> 00:58:00,100
And then what do we see on the right-hand side?

1671
00:58:00,300 --> 00:58:01,160
On the right-hand side,

1672
00:58:01,160 --> 00:58:02,520
we have T,

1673
00:58:02,520 --> 00:58:03,120
R,

1674
00:58:03,120 --> 00:58:05,460
S evaluated

1675
00:58:05,460 --> 00:58:08,320
or its components in the X frame of reference.

1676
00:58:08,940 --> 00:58:12,880
So this little operation has defined for me

1677
00:58:12,880 --> 00:58:14,590
a new class of things

1678
00:58:14,590 --> 00:58:16,300
which are tensors of rank two

1679
00:58:16,300 --> 00:58:18,980
which transform in this manner.

1680
00:58:19,800 --> 00:58:24,140
Notice it's very similar except sort of doubled

1681
00:58:25,540 --> 00:58:28,420
Each time you want to transform an index,

1682
00:58:29,380 --> 00:58:31,700
you get a factor dy by dx.

1683
00:58:32,660 --> 00:58:34,120
For each index,

1684
00:58:34,120 --> 00:58:36,100
here's the index M.

1685
00:58:36,440 --> 00:58:39,960
You have a dyM by dxR,

1686
00:58:39,960 --> 00:58:41,400
and this is a dummy index.

1687
00:58:42,220 --> 00:58:43,860
And then for the N,

1688
00:58:43,860 --> 00:58:46,320
you have a dyn by dxS,

1689
00:58:47,120 --> 00:58:51,440
and then it multiplies the T with the R,

1690
00:58:51,440 --> 00:58:52,160
S index

1691
00:58:52,160 --> 00:58:53,720
in the other frame of reference.

1692
00:58:53,980 --> 00:58:54,800
This is a pattern.

1693
00:58:55,300 --> 00:58:58,220
You could do the same thing for tensors

1694
00:58:58,220 --> 00:59:00,140
with any number of indices up here.

1695
00:59:00,600 --> 00:59:02,720
I'll leave it to you to work out the rules.

1696
00:59:03,680 --> 00:59:04,540
They're easy.

1697
00:59:04,660 --> 00:59:06,420
They're just simple generalizations of this

1698
00:59:06,420 --> 00:59:08,040
where for every index,

1699
00:59:08,040 --> 00:59:10,140
you get another factor like this

1700
00:59:10,140 --> 00:59:13,780
and another index up in the tensor over here.

1701
00:59:14,920 --> 00:59:16,480
That's all a tensor is.

1702
00:59:16,740 --> 00:59:18,760
That's the whole definition of a tensor.

1703
00:59:18,840 --> 00:59:21,020
These tensors are generally functions of position,

1704
00:59:22,540 --> 00:59:24,580
functions of position in general,

1705
00:59:24,760 --> 00:59:27,400
just like vectors can be vector fields

1706
00:59:27,400 --> 00:59:29,200
and vary from place to place.

1707
00:59:30,680 --> 00:59:34,400
But this is the rule for transforming tensors,

1708
00:59:34,420 --> 00:59:35,540
and that's all there is to it.

1709
00:59:35,600 --> 00:59:37,860
There's no other definition of a tensor than this.

1710
